cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.CC 

This paper deals with the concept of skylines in database queries, which is a topic in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also involves the analysis of random samples, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). The study of probability assumptions and threshold phenomena suggests that information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) may also be relevant sub-categories.
